{
  "date": "2026-03-25",
  "title": "Who You Stop For Reveals Who You Are",
  "scriptures": [
    {
      "ref": "Luke 10:33-34",
      "text": "But a Samaritan, as he journeyed, came to where he was, and when he saw him, he had compassion. He went to him and bound up his wounds…."
    }
  ],
  "sections": [
    {
      "key": "read_this_out_loud",
      "label": "Read This Out Loud",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Not everyone who sees…. stops."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Not everyone who feels…. acts."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Compassion is not proven by what you notice."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "It’s proven by what you do next."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "You don’t reveal your character in planned moments."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "You reveal it in interruptions."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "the_devotional",
      "label": "The Devotional",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "A man is beaten, left on the side of the road."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Three men pass by."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Two keep walking."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "One stops."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Same moment."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Different men."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "The difference wasn’t awareness."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "They all saw him."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "The difference was response."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "The priest had knowledge."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "The Levite had position."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "But the Samaritan had compassion that moved him."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Not just something he felt…."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Something he acted on."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "He didn’t just notice the need."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "He stepped into it."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "the_shift",
      "label": "The Shift",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Most men don’t lack compassion."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "They lack margin and willingness."
        },
        {
          "type": "lines",
          "items": [
            "We tell ourselves:",
            "“I don’t have time”",
            "“Someone else will handle it”",
            "“I’ll circle back later”"
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "But compassion doesn’t wait for convenience."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "And over time, something dangerous happens:"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "We start stepping over what God is putting in front of us."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Not because we’re bad…."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "But because we’re preoccupied."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "And preoccupation slowly numbs conviction."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "jesus_set_the_pattern",
      "label": "Jesus Set the Pattern",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "“Go and do likewise.” (Luke 10:37)"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Jesus doesn’t end the story with:"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "“Feel bad for him.”"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "He ends it with:"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "“Go.”"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "This is not about awareness."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "This is about action."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Because love, in the Kingdom, is not theoretical."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "It shows up."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "It steps in."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "It gets involved."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "the_truth",
      "label": "The Truth",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "If you don’t train yourself to stop,"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "you will train yourself to pass by."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "And what you repeatedly pass by,"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "you eventually stop seeing altogether."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "You weren’t made to avoid need."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "You were formed to enter it."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "reflection",
      "label": "Reflection",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "bullet_list",
          "items": [
            "Where have I been too busy to stop?",
            "What have I been stepping over that God is putting in front of me?",
            "Who around me needs presence, not just awareness?"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "declaration",
      "label": "Declaration",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "lines",
          "items": [
            "I will not ignore what God shows me.",
            "I will not pass by what requires love.",
            "I am present, available, and willing to act."
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "action_step",
      "label": "Action Step",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Today, when you feel the nudge, don’t explain it away."
        },
        {
          "type": "lines",
          "items": [
            "👉 Stop.",
            "👉 Lean in.",
            "👉 Do something."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Send the text."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Make the call."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Offer the help."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Stay present."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Don’t overthink it. Just move."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "one_sentence_to_carry",
      "label": "One Sentence to Carry",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "quote",
          "text": "“I don’t pass by what God puts in front of me.”"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "__insert_block_header": "2026-03-25_luke-10-33-34_who-you-stop-for-reveals-who-you-are|"
}
